data.text: There are examples of how to use ordinal numbers at the entry for fifth .

tr: the musical interval between one note and another four notes away from it
number four in a countable series
coming next after the third and just before the fifth in position or time or degree or magnitude
example: the quaternary period of geologic time extends from the end of the tertiary period to the present
fourthly, you must pay the rent on the first of the month

example.ex: Last year's winner Greg Lemond of the United States is in fourth place.
example.tran: 去年的冠军、来自美国的格雷格·莱蒙德现在排名第 4。

value.def: The fourth item in a series is the one that you count as number four.

example.ex: Three-fourths of the public say they favor a national referendum on the issue.
example.tran: 四分之三的公众表示希望就这个问题进行全民公决。

value.def: A fourth is one of four equal parts of something.

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, use 英国英语用quarter

trans: 第四季度；四季度；第四节；第四季

第四维(科学家和科幻小说作家用语，即时间)；非常人的体验
